This importer should open most imagery from DICOM files and copy most of the
metadata into the Opticks metadata. Currently, JPEG2000 will not load
and a few other obscure bit formats may have problems. Also, the metadata is
not interpreted except to convert to the appropriate base type (int, etc.)
when appropriate. There's still quite a bit of work to do as far as metadata
interpretation and testing. This is a good start. JPEG2000 can be supported
with a non-free extension to dcmtk. Maybe we should write an open source
extension for JPEG2000?
